The Jade Magistracy's survey teams have documented the Glasswash Sulfur Fan Colossus occupying the Yellow Garden Colossus Chamber and physically blocking all viable survey approach to the mineral deposit zone. The creature is not merely territorial; Kowloon analysts believe it has assimilated centuries of crystalline mineral accumulation into its body and is anchoring the entire Yellow Garden's ecological pressure. Eliminating it would collapse the hostile element concentration and open the Yellow Garden to survey access.
The Glasswash Sulfur Fan Colossus has been eliminated and Kowloon's survey teams have entered the Yellow Garden for the first time. Initial mineral assessments describe obsidian deposits threaded with crystalline sulfur inclusions and volcanic glass strata that have not been exposed to external atmosphere in recorded history. The Jade Magistracy has classified the preliminary findings and begun drafting a geological survey rights claim under intercity compact law.
